<img src=http://www.myezboard.com/projects/ezboard/ezboard_userimages/theavantguard/images/Athasilly.jpg></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/umorinkhanmt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MorinkhanMT</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Blackburrow Trainee</span><br>  Posts: 63<br> <font color=#628CBC>(9/19/02 5:06:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=21.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Etheral Elixir</span><hr size=1> No, BoA and Marzin's Mark don't stack. Aego overwrites every other direct hp buff in the game now except Khura's Focus (SHM), Brell's (PAL) and our own self buff, Blessed Armour of the Risen. It doesn't overwrite indirect hp buffs, such as Talisman of the Brute, the shaman group STA-buff.<br>
<br>
About acquiring these spells... BoA is readily available nowadays, not sure what they sell for, but it shouldn't be THAT bad. It's one of the best spells a cleric gets, so expect it to be expensive, but it shouldn't be 50k or anything crazy anymore. I'm not our spell-seller though... =P<br>
<br>
Marzin's Mark drops off only one mob in the entire game, the High Priest in Ssra. Only FE, FoV and TW(I think, sorry if I'm wrong TW =P) have killed him. MM drops off him rarely. I think FE currently only has 2-3 copies, I imagine the other guilds are about the same. Since HP is a one-week spawn and all these guilds have 10+ clerics, I'd be shocked to see MM on sale any time in the next several months. I don't even have my own copy yet =P<br>
<br>
BTW, Remove Greater Curse is pretty much the same situation as MM. It only drops off Rhag2, a much easier fight than HP. There are several guilds capable of killing him, but RGC is usable by clerics, druids, shaman and pallies. Most guilds will outfit all their members with the spell first, so I'd be highly surprised to see many copies of RGC on sale for a long time too.<br>
<br>
