 <p><center><img src="http://user.netomia.com/kyley_eq/reignasig.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/umorinkhanmt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MorinkhanMT</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Blackburrow Trainee</span><br>  Posts: 64<br> <font color=#628CBC>(9/20/02 8:32:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=21.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Etheral Elixir</span><hr size=1> Curses were introduced into the game with the Luclin expansion. Therefore, the only zones you'd ever encounter one are on the Moon. =)<br>
<br>
They work exactly the same as other detrimental effects. A curse might DoT you, or DD you, or drain your mana, or slow you, or snare you. The only difference is that to cure the effect, you need to cast Remove Curse instead of Remove Disease or Remove Poison.<br>
<br>
Plus, I could be wrong since I hardly ever xp, but I think curses are primarily seen on raid-class mobs in Luclin. Ssra Temple is full of curses. =) <p>        <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=47567">Morinkhan</a><br>
